radiographic_examinations.findings: Hypointense region in the left basal ganglia suggestive of an ischemic stroke.
Confirmed the presence of an acute infarct in the left caudate head, internal capsule, and putamen.

Absent basilar artery with vertebral arteries terminating in the posterior inferior cerebellar arteries; occlusion of the first segment of the left middle cerebral artery; stenoses at the origins of the brachiocephalic, anterior cerebral, and middle cerebral arteries; extreme tortuosity of the carotid and vertebral arteries.
3-cm soft tissue mass inferior to the right ischial tuberosity.
Occlusion of the horizontal portion of the right middle cerebral artery; right anterior cerebral artery intact.
Hyperintense lesions in the right MCA and ACA territories.
